<h1>Jason Blevins knows the rush of Colorado&#8217;s outdoors, and the economics that make it run</h1>
<hr />
    <p><strong>Jason Blevins</strong> might have the best job ever. We here at Colorado Sun headquarters live vicariously through him and his exploits as he skis, kayaks, strolls and rolls along Colorado&#8217;s trails and rivers to write about our amazing outdoors.</p>

<p>There&#8217;s no one in Colorado journalism who understands both the adrenaline rush and the economics of the outdoor industry that are so important to our state.</p>

<p style="background-color:#fcd232;padding:12px;">We&#8217;re so confident that you&#8217;ll enjoy his weekly newsletter The Outsider that<strong> we want to give you a two-week free trial.</strong> Or, skip the trial and become a <a target="_blank"  href="http://coloradosun.com/join">Premium Sun member right now! </a>For just $20 a month, you&#8217;ll also get our exclusive newsletters on <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/temperature/?pico=clean">climate, health</a> and <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/unaffiliated/?pico=clean">politics</a>!</p>

<p>But enough from me. Read below to hear why Jason is so fired up about producing this coverage for you.</p>

